reviews.review_text:
THIS IS NOT A MAFIA GAME.
The game by itself is fine. It's actually decent but the sheer amount of things I noticed while playing (and probably other people might feel this way as well) cannot be ignored:
- There are some technical issues like soft locks you can witness during some story mission cutscenes or while trying to speak with your informants after completing the damage for a racket, some audio pieces being muted from time to time or hmm... THE 17 GLITCHY ACHIEVEMENTS! (sadly S.A.M.);
(These next one may be nitpicks but bare with me)
- The story actually not having its "Mafia" formula. Sure it has the little bit with the betrayal from Giorgi and his father and we actually form intentionally/unintentionally our own mafia but it doesn't feel like the last two games. And the story itself isn't as bad as some may say (that's how I felt);
- It has sooo many mechanics from different games that made me scratch my head a bit: the slow-mo on cars similar with Franklin's slow from GTAV or the speedbreaker from NFS:MW, the slow-mo shooting like Michael's slow, again GTAV, or the focus slow from Watchdogs or the whole "empire" stuff similar to GTA:VCS. It made the game lose its identity with these things, especially when it removed the most important aspect that was in general a Mafia standard: the speed limit. It felt too boring driving at high speed without the cops reacting and trying to punish me for it. Heck, you can't even get pulled over;
- The whole racket system is a chore. Sure it was alright in the first three primary districts of each underboss but the tasks are exactly the same, same things: interrogate informants, kill enforcers, destroy stuff and/or steal cash, afterwards get the racket, repeat. Too boring especially in new playthroughs.

But the game is good when it's good:
- As mentioned previously the story is actually good, different from what Mafia is in general but good. I like it more than Mafia II. Plus the documentary/recordings segments in some cutscenes were really neat;
- Lincoln was a pretty good protagonist. He gave me a ACIII Connor vibe but MUCH much better than Connor. Also Donovan gave me a Mike Toreno (S.A.) vibe but much funnier. We want another Donovan DLC;
- The story missions outside of the racket mechanic are actually cool and even the DLCs are cool as well, especially Stones Unturned;
- The game looks good as for now and even made a standard for Mafia I D.E. to look even better.

So Mafia III is a wasted potential. If it was a new game not related to the franchise whatsoever, removing Vito, Leo and the Commission and replace them with totally different stuff + if the game had a different name, then it would have been above average. If it was also fixed in some technical areas, then it would have been good and if it didn't had so many mechanics from other games or at least a small number of them, then it would have been great. As for me, I find the game being below average. And hopefully I might not farm districts ever again. And finally done with the "trilogy".
